e sooner society recognizes the reality of climate change risk, the more effectively we can begin adaptation to limit costs to present and future generations. They show that climate risk presents a new opportunity for innovation, supporting aspirations for prosperity in a lower carbon, climate altered future where we can continue economic progress without endangering the environment and ourselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aClimatic changesxCalifornia. 0aClimatic changesxEconomic aspectsxCalifornia. 0aClimatic changesxEconomic aspectszCalifornia. 0aClimatic changesxEnvironmental aspectsxCaliforniaxCalifornia. 0aClimatic changeszCalifornia. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Meteorology & Climatology.2bisacsh1 aRoland-Holst, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520953802.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles